\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Our local builder who's been doing a little bit of work for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Oh, yes, and, um, then it was emptied and taken down the garden, you see, at certain time, when we got fairly full up, you see, all the rubbish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you grow all the produce you needed in the way of vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Mostly I think we did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Who used to work the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, father and my brothers, you see, and I took an interest in it when I was old enough. Er, when my, when I was at school (..) \{BLANK
\} used to help a little bit with the, on Saturdays, with the, er, wheelwright's work, you know, making (..) changes er, for the farm carts, when they, er, the tyres for the farm carts, they were not, er, er, have you read Sturt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I've read some of it, yes. I didn't read it all;
 I found it a bit difficult to understand in some places it's very technical. Yes, I expect you would. Well, I don't think there's anything (..) of that in there, but the, the heavy farm carts, erm, they used on the land (?), er, tumbrils, they'd have (..
)
 sheaks, sheaks on, segments of iron, not a whole, not a complete tyre, you see. If you've got the fourteen spoke wheel, there'd be the seven, er, segments, you see, and the gap left between each segment, because um, farm carts standing up in dry, hot wea
t
her whole tyres would get loose very quickly, you see, and these segments prevent, er, if they got a little bit loose they wouldn't push each other off. There was always a little gap between. I've got one old "streak" they used to call them, s-t-r-e-a-k, 
and the big nails \{BLANK\} used to do them, we used to, er, do them at home, put them on (..) when the wheels were ready, you see, er..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You mean, you wouldn't do that in the workshop? You'd do that in your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Outside in the yard, we'd a bi
g yard, you see, and fire (..) wood, and, er, put these, they had fitted, just fitted round first, and marked and just, er, numbered and so on, and, er, and then, um, with a huge fire in the yard, put the streaks in. When they were hot father would get a 
big, er, pair of tongs he'd lift, lift one out and, the wheel would be, er, (..) at an angle, you see, on a big block, with the, um, so you could put, big block and, um,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16197746\charrsid8658109 
 where the axle (..) There\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109  be a, um, bit of wood stick up so you could twist the wheel
 round, you see, where you wanted, and, er; then we'd get a start with er, smaller, a heavy hammer, but a small one, get a start and then, er, one end, then he'd let the, er, tyre, take the tongs away, and you'd get a start with the other end of the strea
k, and then, er, then you'd go at it hammer and tongs, as they say, with the sledge hammers, you see, and, then, er, the, you, er, first where the, the joints were in between, you see, the, er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7936078\charrsid8658109 
, joints of the (..) (felloes?)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109  or (}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7936078\charrsid8658109 ..) (fellies?) (..) (fellies?)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
 we used to call them, and, er, then, you'd, you'd twist the wheel round, you'd have, er, water handy and we'd have to squench (?) them in the water, clouds of steam of course, and you could hear the joints cracking up as they strained you see, tighten, t
ighten the joints up, and, er,
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You used to call them (fellies?) did you say, because in that book they're called fellows aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, yes, we used, that is the, the proper spelling, you see, we used to call them (fellies?), and, er, the..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you help do that, then, when you were a boy? You used to help in that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, yes, well ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Before you, when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, er, I expect I stopped on another year, I think. I've got an old school certificate of leaving, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You left after Standard 4, didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Has successfully passed the fourth standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 But, before you left school, did you help you father then with some of the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Er, odds and end, what jobs I could do, making (..)
 plugs and (..) helps and bells, in the fellows (?), er, in the joints er, they have, er, wooden, wooden dells (?). You wouldn't, you don't understand what I mean, but .. pins, er, in the joint, you see, you get, er, you get big pins, and, well, I used to
 make those you see, the dells (?) sharpen them, plane them, plane them up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 How old were you when you first started helping with jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I was about fourteen, fifteen, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Can you remember, when you were a child, did you have other duties in the house you had to do, regular things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, occasionally cleaning on a (..) knife board on a Saturday, clean them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you have to do it every Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Mother.. More-or-less, I suppose, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did the other children all have jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Well, er, my sisters, you see, were away. The older sister was away in service. She married, she was living at Twickenham, she married a painter, not a very, not a very good husband, you know. I think drink was a problem, but she 
was, er, and she used to go out cooking at different ones, you know, round people that she had been with in service. They'd want her to go, do cooking for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And the other sister, did she also go into service?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And, er, er, no, the other sist
ers, Jinny, I told you she was home and the other sister when we started off the Post Office, she ran that, you see, and the telegraph instrument. Well, er, the Post Office was open then, you see, eight in the morning till eight at night. I think I did te
ll you, didn't I, about delivering the telegrams?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You told me about your delivery round..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, er, the letters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You didn't tell me about telegrams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, well, um, we used to deliver, they had to pay }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8798971\charrsid8658109 \{ILLEGIBLE\}}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109  (?) the people, you see, o
ver a mile, fourpence, then for a mile and a half it's sixpence. Over two miles, they had to pay a shilling, and they provided no bicycles, then, you see, erm, you just had to walk, er, sometimes, just on eight o'clock at night you'd have a, a telegram in
 
the depth of winter. As I say the, some gentleman, a Mr. Bligh (?) at Lays Lodge used to go with the stag hounds, hunting, you see. If, er, if it was frosty they'd, um, he'd get a telegram to say they wouldn't be hunting, it was too hard, too frosty, you 
see, but you'd have to go about two miles (..) \{BLANK\} after {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
, and you'd be fairly young then, and a certain part of the, um, journey there was a, oh, supposed to be a will o' the wisp, the old pear tree at Little Legs (?) on the way to (..) Fe
lsted you always used to whistle to keep your spirits up, when you were walking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you believe it? That there might be a will o' the wisp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, not really (..) I don't think...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Were your parents superstitious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, they didn't, certain things they didn't like in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 What were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Er, certain flower, what was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Was it lilac? Some people believe lilac to be unlucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No. No, something, something else, I forget what it was now, they didn't, they didn't
 like in the house. May, the may was supposed, not supposed to be very lucky, I don't think, no, the, and, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Were there any other superstitions you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Superstitions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did they do things like throwing salt over their shoulder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Oh, yes, over your left shoulder, throw a piece of salt you're your left shoulder. They were not superstitious about colours; some people wouldn't have green in the house, would they? And, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Walking under a ladder, some people would never do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, underneath ladders, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
That always seems quite sensible, of course, because you might get a pot of paint dropped on you something like that if you were walking underneath. But now tell me, did you spend a lot of time with your brothers and sisters when you were young children?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, when, the, er, only time I used to see them, when they came for holidays, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 But when you were a very little child, say, four, five, six years old, a lot of them must have still been at home, weren't t
hey? Some of them would have still been at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No, only the, er, second one, Mary, the one I've got, still got living at East \{ILLEGIBLE\}
, and, er, she went out to service at Little Legs Hall, you see, and, er, she lived in there, I think she had a, a shilling a month, I think, living in there, and then, er,..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And what about the brother who was ten when you were born, where was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, eventually he, er, he left home}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8798971\charrsid8658109  and he (..) was the estate car}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 penter for the Trittons at Lyons Hall, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 But when you were a little boy, say, about four years old, and he was about fourteen or thirteen, would he have been at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Um, yes, my brothers were both at home then, you see, my older brother didn't marry until fairly late really. I was nearly grown up.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 So, though the sisters weren't there, the brothers were at home when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes. Yes we all at home, you see, and there was just the two big bedrooms and the little one, er, and as I got older I got tra
nsferred to, er, the top room over the, um, there were three staircases, one old room, er, over the kitchen part, over the scullery part, um, we, um, I were transferred to there, you see, father was sleeping there, and slept there, and, er, and my mother 
and two sisters had the big bedroom, and, er, then my brothers had the other room at the back, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did every child have his own bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 The, er, side of the bedrooms, where that big chest used to stand, all along the side, you know, the big oak chest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did each of the children have their own bed? or did they have to share?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Oh, er, they, their own bed. I shared, you see, but when I, when I was growing up, you see, with father, I slept with him, and, er, mother and sisters; they used the
 old-fashioned warming pan to warm the beds. You'd think you were being burnt, and the pan would be cold. Er, you've seen those of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I have seen those, yes, I've seen those. What time did you have to get up in the morning when you were a school boy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Er, well, one wasn't always so keen on getting up, to go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did your father get up early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes, he was always first one up, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And when he got up, would he make anything in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 He would go, he would s
ee about the fire, you see, go down the yard, or perhaps, er, they'd start work in the workshop, come into breakfast, in the summertime, in the, er, the summer the streaks I was talking about, shoeing those wheels, um, we'd, er, was very hot weather, he'd
 probably get up, you see, and, er, that's when I was older, as well, they'd shoe a set of wagon wheels before breakfast, before it got too hot, you see, and get those done, and in the winter time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You mean, that would be about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Oh, yes. In the wintertime, er, when you couldn't, very practical to have a fire outside to heat the streaks, we'd, we'd heat them indoors, this scullery place, I told you below the oven door, there was a low, er, hearth, you see, and, er, it was
 big enough to hold the streaks to, er, used to heat them in there, then you'd have to bring them outside and the tongs red-hot, and, er,
