Simons. I think one of the old lady's daughters, I would really think, er, I don't remember the mother, the girl's mother \{BLANK\} the old Lady Simons and, er, the son, he ran the farm, Mr. Simons, and, er, I think she was (..) \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 really the daughter, you know, nice girl, and she married and lived at Cowes, the Isle of Wight, and then the farmer, when the old lady died, he had a housekeeper, a hunting housekeeper, she used to ride, go hunting, er,..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 But, I was asking you if you'd had, I mean, did you enjoy your schooldays, and did you like schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Yes, I really liked it, I liked geography, I think as well as anything. They said I always had my hand up. The schoolmaster's daughter, er, his name was Rudes, she's still living at Kings Lynn, I heard she was crippled, but I only met her once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 The board school that you went to, was that just the one school you stayed at all the time, you didn't change schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And how many children were there in your class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
I don't remember really how many, good many altogether, mm. We had to take, er, er, older ones, we were called monitors, we had to take a class you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Were you a monitor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes. Take a, there was a small classroom where the tiny ones were, you'd
 teach them, er, twice one's are two, twice two's are four, you know, all right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I didn't mind, really, and, er, .. I remember I didn't like, er, we used to, arithmetic, sum, maths you call them now, don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You didn't like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I didn't care, I wasn't very good at, used to rather dread the inspector, I believe I mentioned (..) that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You did mention the inspections, yes. Did your parents take an interest in your school work, and your progress at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, father did, well, of course, father could read and write but his father, my grandfather, was a splendid writer..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes, because he was a clerk wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Father wasn't so good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And your mother..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, mother didn't do much writing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 But she could read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes. Er, a bit, she didn't do much reading, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 But was there ever any..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 She was very b-, I mean so busy like, you see, with a large family, with the cooking and the mangling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you get along well with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Mother used to go gleaning, too, in the cornfields, you see, and pea picking. I used to go out with, when I, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 (Mr. Taylor).. school day, they had pea picking holidays then, you see, not the, not the different..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You mean they'd give a holiday from the school at pea picking time, would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 For how long would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Fortnight, or would be as, or, nearly as long, not so long in the summer holidays, we didn't get about three weeks, I think
, and the peak picking, we'd go out in the fields, early morning, you'd be crying with cold, almost, you know, cold and wet, and then later on there'd be the sun come out and it was really hot, but, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did your mother go out pea picking for the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, er, they'd go out pea picking till come home about three, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 4}}}four o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And then she had to do her housework, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Take some, take some food.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Would she do her housework when she came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, well, yes, yes, what there was to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did she have anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No, oh, no, oh, no. Yes, she worked very hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Would you say compared with other people around you, were you hard up, or average, or better than average for money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, not much, not much money. My brother kept a pony, you see. He used to let that out to, for people to hire, if they wanted to go to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. He'd have a pony and cart to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} and back, half a crown, seven miles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And the wheelwright's business, how did that do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Pardon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Was it a success?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Well, it was hardly, just enough to keep going, that's all. They said father never charged enough, and sometimes used to have to wait two years before you get your money, some..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Because I noticed in George Sturt's book, he says how certain kinds of the work he was doing, you know, didn't even pay its way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No, oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Do you think your father, did his work fail, because George Sturt seemed to feel that with the chang
ing times the wheelwright's business was playing less and less. Do you think your father felt this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 The wheelwright's pay..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 That he was losing, I mean, I felt George Sturt felt he was losing ground, I think, in some ways, and so he had to go ov
er to machinery, didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Oh, yes, um, he didn't, well, they just rubbed along. I think my elder brother when, when, um, father would send his bill in, you see, and, er, there were those who paid, er, I think father would share the money out, the o
lder brother, the other brother, until he went (..) here you see, or, and then, they'd do little odd jobs on their own, I expect, you see and all like that, um, make up, er, my, er, second brother, he'd make up a light cart, er, you know with odd times, y
ou see and he'd sell it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you do anything to bring in a bit of extra money when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Er, you mean, to bring money in..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 For pocket money, or for money for the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No, I don't think so, no wasn't much in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you have pocket money at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I used to get half a crown a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Half a crown a week? That was good, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Eh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Half a crown a week..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, er, for some work, working..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, for work, I see, I meant pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 for working in the workshop. Oh, no. (..) \{BLANK\} that'd be a farthing or a penny. We'd go up to the sweet shop, the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Victoria{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and buy some, oh, and then at St. Anne's Castle they had the annual fair, you see, Whitmonday Fair, had its stalls there and the (..) \{
