\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes, they were not so, when, er, ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 more strict in the country, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, when, er, \{BLANK\} when I, when the war, er, she was staying with her aunt at Great Les, she was staying for her holidays \{BLANK\}
 we were supposed to be in by nine o'clock, you see. Go out for walks and Sunday afternoon, and, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And she'd like you, her to be home by nine, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And, um, but you could go out any evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 (..) \{BLANK\} and then spend part of the evening, you see, er at the village stores and shops, you see, spend part of the evening..

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And did she go to your own home too, for tea and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, yes, and, er, we'd go for long walks, you see walks all round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 It's a nice way to spend the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11685387\charrsid8658109 think I told you that Dr. (..) {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}C}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 lark{\*\xmlclose} the old Rector; at Great Leas was very interested in the old papers and that, you know, the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, er, you, um, you did train at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 .. thing about my brothers, some of the old pony. Did I, I haven't mentioned the old, had I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You told me that your brother, one of your brothers had a pony and trap that he used to hire out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 That's right, yes, yes. Used to hire out, yes. Well, er, the two brothers and myself, when I was younger too, er, (..) \{BLANK\}
 feed the pony in the winter, we'd got no meadows, you see. The farmers, er, er, used to let us have, well, I didn't know what it actually meant then, I was pretty young, dools dools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Dools, how do you spell that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Dools. D double-O, well since then it's probably it's doles d-o-l-e-s, the farmer's doles, you see. They let us have the, um, the rough hay round the edges of the corn fields (..) the ditches and round the fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 They used to let you have this rough hay, for the pony.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Yes, we used to cart it home in the pony cart, you see, and shake it around, we had a big, er, yard, well, you saw where the old newspaper (..
) photograph the, um ground run right down to the bottom of the place, and, er, there was a footpath right at the bottom, er, running down to the little river, the river (..) \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 name from it, you see, and, er, we used to, er, the farmer would let us after (..) \{BLANK\}
 the when the river was, a big flood, it would come up to the, almost to the bottom of our gardens, you see, with meadow, meadow ground (round?) and, er, the farmer would let us cut that bit where it had been flooded, well, er, one sim
ple reason apart from it being flooded, it'd be all \{BLANK\} you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 It would be all what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Grit. Grit and dust, and after it had been flooded. Well they had the job of cutting, cutting some of that, you'd got to sharpen your scytheevery, every 
little, every few minutes, almost. Very difficult to cut you see, but, er, and then I, in addition I told you my brother let the pony out, didn't I, to people who wished to hire it a day (..) half a crown a day, um, if they wanted to be driven, it was my 
job to drive, drive the vehicle, you see. We used to charge three shillings then. I don't think I got any money, actually, I just had the honour of driving people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 So the three shillings went to your brother, did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Pardon? Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Didn't he give you anything for doing the driving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Um, not to my recollection, no, I don't think so. I had the privilege of looking after the pony and, each morning and feeding and..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, I didn't mind, yes. We had two or three different ponies and, er, my brother also \{BLANK\}
 he contracted for the police, instead of a little car, while they have now a police car, they used to, the local policeman lived opposite us, and, er, they used to have the pony cart when they ha
d the gallery wood Races, to drive the odd pony, and on the way he used to collect three or four other policemen, you see and they used to drive through to gallery wood they were on duty at the races. Er, you can imagine the old pony cart, four or five bi
g
 policemen in; one old pony, he used to say his prayers nearly every time he went out, go down on his knees, you know, he always wore knee caps, but you know, none of them went down when I was driving, other people not very good drivers, and all like that
 you know, and, er,
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And you had the three, three ponies, you say, usually. There were three ponies, were there, usually, that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, er, different times, only one at a time. We did have two at one time, my brother bought an {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Exmoor{\*\xmlclose} pony, in the market, and er, between us, and we broke that in, you see, it was quite a young pony, broke it in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And if you and your family wanted to go somewhere to visit people, did you go in the pony cart too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 It was the family means of transport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 There was the policeman who, er, moved to (..) \{BLANK\} to (..) Little Baddon and, er, we all went over in the pony cart after he \{BLANK
\} We took a little, er, barrow, the policeman's, er, boy, you see. It was one I think they used to have about, it w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11685387\charrsid8658109 as painted up. We took it over L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 ittle (..) Baddon for the policeman, and, er, they, er, from Chelmsford they only had one mounted policeman, then, Marshall, his name was, he used to drive the police dog cart, you see, and the deputy ch
ief used to ride round with him, and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11685387\charrsid8658109  the policeman's name was (..) C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
ole and, er, when he'd come up, we used to call out (Coal, Cole??) \{BLANK\} as though he was selling (..) Coal That was the only, the only mounted police they had, and, er,
