 two daughters (..) Dr Clark had two daughters, and, er, one was a very lively young lady, and, er, the other one, well, she was going to, er, I think she was going to, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}
}Australia{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, or something or other. Anyway, on board ship, she met another, er, she'd met a clergyman, and she married him, they went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}
South Africa{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} (..) I believe she's still living near Cambridge when
 I heard last, and the elder daughter, was, er, very lively, and, um, (..) there's a hymn Christian dost thou see them (him?), you know, one of the Lent hymns, and, er, do, er, do you know much of the Church?
