\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 When your mother went pea-picking, I think you said you went with her.. Is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes, occasionally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Were there a lot of other children there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes. They'd be crying with cold, first thing. Early mornings, you k
now, when the dew - always start early because they had to load the peas up and get them on the rail, you see, then, there's no lorries to pick them up, and, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did the children all keep together in the field, or did they..?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Some people, some 
of them had prams, you see, you'd have a, you'd pick, you'd more-or-less have your own stretch you see. You wouldn't all pick at one spot you see, work down, you know the fields how they're laid out in stretches, don't you? Strips, er, furrow, and then a 
strip erm, you'd, understand better, than some of the old wheelwrighting, I think (..) the (..) I suppose the worthtrees and the set sticks and the horses, and, er, yes, they'd work on those, and..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And the children would, where would the children be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 \{BLANK\} they'd help pick, they'd have a pail, you see, they'd help pick the peas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You used to help pick the peas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes. Yes, and they'd knock off, I suppose, about, er, two or three o'clock and come home, and you were, well, you were allowed
 to, most of them had, er, spare peas, if they had any left over and they'd tied the bag, were allowed to, they were allowed to take them home, you see. Strictly speaking, they shouldn't, they do now in the fields, strictly speaking, they shouldn't take t
h
em home, and the farmer we were speaking about, the John Bull one, he would tell us, er, we could have, if he had a field of turnips, we could go and help ourselves, you see; used to do the work for him at the workshop, and also, after the pea, after the 
pea-picking had finished, the other farmer or the other farmers, you were allowed to go and glean, er, peas, the stray ones, you know heaps and heaps of stray where there were a lot picked Pea (..) \{BLANK\}
 pea-rice, you see, you took (..) REIS you'd call it (..) pea-rice..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Pea-rice you call it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Rice. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Were a lot of families allowed to do that, or just your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, A lot of (..) them all round to do the pea-picking. A good many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 But the gleaning, did they all have the right to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you ever in the evenings, at home, have a sing-song or anyone play the piano in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 my elder sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 She had an American organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, we had the, I think I told you, we had the (..) \{ILLEGIBLE\} dance hall, and this, er, (..) \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 the people, he came over and taught us. I think it was seven and six an evening, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you have your own violin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes. Oh, yes, I looked to, er, the antique dealer in the street, Mr. (..) Billeys \{BLANK\}
 er, he wanted two bows, violin bows, they had two bows, and, er, the violin was knocking about upstairs. I hadn't touched it, and the wooden case was getting worm-eaten. I decided to get rid of it you see, and, er, so he had that and he h
ad, um, an old ratchet pothook thing that they used to hang up on the chimneys. When I was about on the buildings, you see, they used to throw, throw stuff away on the heap, the rubbish heap outside, mortar and rubbish, when they were building, and, er, t
his old pothook and ratchet was a thing they used to have, hang up in the chimney, you see, hang the big pot on, \{BLANK\} the ratchet just like a \{BLANK\}
 you could adjust it up or down, you see, to, er, to, if you wanted the pot lower or higher, you see. Er, oh, yes, he had the old violin and, er, and also, er, (..) gurka..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 How old were you when you got that violin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Er, Don't know now, I used to play a little bit, I went down to (..) Little Walthan once. They used to have what they called pleasant
 Sunday afternoons or pleasant Sunday evenings (..) I'd so do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580324\charrsid8658109 wn and, er, to the (..) Little W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 althan chapel. I went once (..) \{
BLANK\} playing the violin, and, er, with others, and, er, with others, and, er, used to play a little bit at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did it cost a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I think it was three or four pounds, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Were you earning money, then, when you bought it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, well, yes, a little \{BLANK\} only what I could pick up with the telegrams and post, post office.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you pay for it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You saved up, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did the other brothers and sisters, you said one sister had an organ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Ah, yes, and er, well, we could, we could, we could go and play ourselves, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You all played something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 In the front room, they called it. Oh, yes, er, Minnie used, er, she'd got a lovely voice, soprano voice,..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And the other brothers, did they play something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Er, no, they didn't, er, no, they didn't (..) occasionally, if there were one or two friends in, we'd (..) sing do hymns \{BLANK\}
 and I used to practise on the organ one hymn
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 180 I could manage with both hands. Are you musical yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No, I love music but unfortunately, I can't play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 My sister had the mandolin you see. She used to play, and, er,
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you sing other songs besides sacred and religious ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, more-or-less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 What sort of songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 We used to play more-or-less, like what you'd call sentimental, the old songs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you sing any folk songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Er, no, not many folk songs. We took part in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}East Essex{\*\xmlclose} musical festival.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes, that's in your piece, isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Yes, we used to enjoy those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did your mother and father play an instrument or sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No. No, o
riginally, I think they, father, or one of them they had kind of an orchestra in the church, and I think they got a little, based organ that used to be in the church. It went across to (..) hymn hall to the less Trittons, and I think they've given it back
 to the church. I suppose it's there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
You mentioned that when you went to see your prospective father-in-law, you know, when you wanted to get married, you had to show him your post office book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, I didn't have to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Sorry, I mean, it was the thing to do, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 (..) \{BLANK\} Well, I wanted to show I'd got a little behind me. Probably around }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7225249 \'a3}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 200, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 When you first wanted to get engaged you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, well (..)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And did you go on saving over the years you were waiting to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, yes. Then, of course, the, the, er, war came along, and, er,..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 And did your wife save too, and make things, clothes and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, twelve and six a week teaching, paid her lodging money, and then at home, I mean, not much saving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did she make things? Sometimes girls in those days used to make..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No, I don't think so, not in that way. Oh, it's not easy, er, but I settled down after the first (..) World war it's not an 
easy time, and then we had bad spells of unemployment, you know, the building tade, it \{ILLEGIBLE\} (?) all over the place, cycling to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
, when they were building generally up there, and, er, or to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. There'd be several of us, (..) \{BLANK\} 
there was a big slump (..) to help a bit to, um, er, help my brother a bit, you see, with the wheel-wrighting, lend a hand.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 How old were you when you first started work? I know you said you \{BLANK\} but I'm not sure if you told me how old you were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Well, er, you could leave then I suppose at thirteen, fourteen. I suppose it must have been..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Did you start work straightaway then with your brothers and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Do you remember how you felt about starting work, and did you have any..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
No, I would rather like the, you know, the book work I think I took to, bit too particular perhaps over, over some jobs, but, er, the finish, and all like that, perhaps spend too much time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 But you liked working with your brothers and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 You got along well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
Oh, yes, yes there was no friction, not about the, not about the work. My father used to let us go as we please, and er, I could go into, er, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 on a Saturday night, the territor-, the drill hall there. The first year in the territorials, it counted as two (..) drills, you see, if you went into the drill hall, and did a bit of, er, you know (..) minitime rifle shooting, and..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 When you say he let you go in on Saturday night, would you normally have perhaps been working on a Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 
What? (Question repeated) Oh, well, I mean, he didn't raise any difficulties about going out in the evenings, or what time I came home. If we went to the local dances or socials, I'd probably come home, well, perhaps it might be one or 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 2}}}two o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, you see, and then up again for the post round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 When you started work, did you give your mother any of the money? I know you didn't earn much, but I wondered if you gave her any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I had none to give mother, you see, I didn't get any actual wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 Oh, you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8668315 HT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 No, not for the work itself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11482670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11813394\charrsid8658109 I thought you mentioned half-a-crown a week. Was that just..?
